wdi2-SL.TLF.CACT.FM.ZS.def: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period. Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate is calculated by dividing female labor force participation rate by male labor force participation rate and multiplying by 100.
wdi2-SL.TLF.CACT.FM.ZS.name: Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate
wdi2-SL.TLF.CACT.FM.ZS.source: Derived using data from International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. The data retrieved on June 15, 2021.
